messages.message:
@ayesha.ali so on the FE we have a bunch of these FE input errors for class and field names. This is actually meant for manual generation when user input need to be converted into python-safe variable names in the backend.

The errors actually got triggered for me twice in a span of maybe ~12 attempts. One is in the screenshot below, the other was "field name cannot exceed 48 characters". I was wondering it might be better to handle this on the BE/model side? Currently, there is no workaround in FE but to add a regenerate schema button. cc @Serena
Ah yup I can add those restraints to the prompt
lmk if you need other restraints that might be on the FE! I haven't dug too deeply into it
